title: 820-3462 not starting
message:
Hi Guys,

I have a 820-3462 that does not start up, no liquid damage it just stopped working. All voltages are present but on L7510 and L7520 i get only 0.7v instead of 1.25. I have checked U7400 its powered at pin 46 at 5V. CPUIMVP TON A and B have 12.35, r7402 and 03 are 181k ohm so seems OK too. L7550 gives 0 reading. I saw in a video from Lewis that Ton A and B often fail but it seems to be working here. How should I go about to troubleshoot this?

All other voltages are OK.

title: 820-3462 not starting
message:
It IS starting because you have CPU Vcore. 0.7V is fine there.
Does a USB  mouse light up when plugged in? Fan spinning?
